item.description:
When deploying my laravel site that use Vite and sass (CSS-preprocessor), I got this error &quot; Unable to locate file in Vite manifest: resources/sass/app.sass&quot;
Turns out, I need to update the vite config file
import { defineConfig } from &#39;vite&#39;; import laravel from &#39;laravel-vite-plugin&#39;; export default defineConfig({ plugins: [ laravel({ input: [ &#39;resources/sass/app.sass&#39;, &#39;resources/js/app.js&#39;, ], refresh: true, }), ], }); To that. or whatever the name of your sass file is
